<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99970667082016></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99970667082016><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=quest.html?quest=1258&mid=99970667082016>Tailoring</a> <a id=fs8 href=quest.html?quest=1258&mid=99970667082016#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=30179><span id= >Andred</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 5th 12:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have been messing around with these No Drop threads in Velk's to see if it would raise my abismal Tailoring skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;They usually just rot since the avg group has no one working on this part of the shawl quest.  I collected 25 silks and with my (39) tailoring skill, went to work.  Results:  Sucess on first try, increased skill to 40;  Second, failed, increased skill to 41;  Third Sucess; Forth Sucess, skill goes to 42; Fifth try failed again, no increase.<br><br>The only advantage I had during my attempts was a pretty massive Dex buff (186 ) I got from a shammy.  This, we are told be the illustrious Niami at eqtraders, will have a positive effect on your chance of skill increases but not on sucessfully tailoring the item.  Thus, it would appear you don't need a very high tailoring skill to complete this quest. <br><br>BTW, does anyone know of any tailoring recipes that use these Crystaline Silk Fibers that result or is it strickly to combine with the bile for the quest shawl?  I tried matching a mask pattern with one and two of the CSF's and got the "will not combine" in this type of container message.  Pretty much what I expected.<br>&nbsp;<br>Andred D'Nocte<br>Knight of Paineel<br>- Fennin Ro - </td></tr>
