	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 21st 3:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.88]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>That's a common misconception...actually your wis or int is the primary stat that determines whether or not you improve your skill with each attempt.&nbsp;&nbsp;For tailoring, dexterity provides a bonus to wis or int to give you a greater chance of gaining skill.  (For smithing, strength does the same thing.)  The ONLY thing that determines whether or not you actually succeed is your level of skill in whatever trade skill you are doing.  In other words a tailor who is at 250 tailoring has absolutely no use whatsoever for dexterity or int/wis.  <br><br>If my word is not enough ;) go here: <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm61.showMessage?topicID=3.topic" target=_new>http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm61.showMessage?topicID=3.topic</a> for more details from EQ Traders, the best EQ tradeskill resource anywhere.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
